dpaa1: board 0104a — advertise NETIF_F_HW_TC so the policer offload is reachable (M3-3d)

Board 0104 added the .ndo_setup_tc TC_SETUP_BLOCK handler that maps an
ingress `tc filter matchall action police` onto fman_policer_install
slot 0, but the DPAA netdev never advertised NETIF_F_HW_TC. With the
feature flag absent, tc_can_offload(net_dev) is false, so the tc core
never routes the matchall filter to the handler:

  * a `skip_sw` filter (the productive path used by the vyos-1x-025
    `set interfaces ethernet ethX ingress-policer` CLI) is rejected
    outright with "Error: TC offload is disabled on net device";
  * a non-`skip_sw` filter installs software-only (`not_in_hw`) and the
    handler is never invoked (no fman_policer_install, no in_hw).

Verified on hardware 2026-06-07 (DUT 192.168.1.190, ISO
2026.06.07-1957-rolling, kernel 6.18.34-vyos): `ethtool -k eth3` showed
`hw-tc-offload: off [fixed]` even though the FMan PCD caps report POL
(`fsl_dpa dpaa-ethernet.0: FMan PCD caps = 0x17 (CC HM POL PARSER)`),
and a matchall police filter ran in software (`not_in_hw rule hit 25`).

Advertise NETIF_F_HW_TC in dpaa_netdev_init(), gated on the same runtime
policer capability the 0104 handler enforces (fman_policer_caps_supported),
mirroring the existing fman_hm_caps_supported() / NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX
pattern a few lines above. This makes hw-tc-offload toggleable+on, so
both skip_sw and non-skip_sw matchall filters reach dpaa_setup_tc()'s
TC_SETUP_BLOCK branch; dpaa_setup_tc_block_cb() still fail-softs every
unsupported tc type with -EOPNOTSUPP, so no other tc offload is exposed.
Touches only dpaa_netdev_init() (no overlap with 0104's setup_tc hunks),
so it stacks cleanly after 0104 and is byte-stable across 6.18.33/6.18.34.

diff --git a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
index 3c4a5b6d..7e8f9a0b 100644
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/freescale/dpaa/dpaa_eth.c
@@ -245,6 +245,19 @@ static int dpaa_netdev_init(struct net_device *net_dev,
 	 */
 	if (fman_hm_caps_supported())
 		net_dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_HW_VLAN_CTAG_RX;
+	/* Policer offload (spec sec 5.6 / board 0104): advertise NETIF_F_HW_TC
+	 * so tc_can_offload() is true and the tc core routes an ingress
+	 * `matchall action police` filter to dpaa_setup_tc()'s TC_SETUP_BLOCK
+	 * handler (-> fman_policer_install slot 0). Without it the netdev shows
+	 * `hw-tc-offload: off [fixed]`, skip_sw filters are rejected ("TC
+	 * offload is disabled on net device") and non-skip_sw filters install
+	 * software-only (not_in_hw). Gated on the runtime policer cap so
+	 * mainline-ucode boards never expose an offload the FMan can't perform;
+	 * dpaa_setup_tc_block_cb() still fail-softs unsupported tc types with
+	 * -EOPNOTSUPP.
+	 */
+	if (fman_policer_caps_supported())
+		net_dev->hw_features |= NETIF_F_HW_TC;
 	/* The kernels enables GSO automatically, if we declare NETIF_F_SG.
 	 * For conformity, we'll still declare GSO explicitly.
 	 */
 	net_dev->features |= NETIF_F_GSO;
